reviewText:
One of the best games and simply the best quest I've played.
Immersive and gloomy noir-cyberpunk atmosphere;
Pixel but very cozy and stylish graphics;
Very interesting plot with awesome twists, I literally finished the game in one breath;
Awesome voice acting, especially the main character's voice;
logical and obvious puzzles, some of them really made me laugh, like:
[computer not working]
[uses his leg on the panel]
[punches the panel]
[computer begins to work];10 out of 10 would recommend anyone who loves noir/cyberpunk setting to buy this game and support the developer.

After finishing this in 2 sittings straight, I cannot recommend this game enough. One of the best story based and point and click adventure games. The puzzles were, if not, the best ones that I have done so far in any video game -  EVERYTHING  fits perfectly and I never got stuck in it at all. However, some puzzles requires a bit of exploring and pixel hunting but at the very least. Wonderful twists and turns in the story line almost left me crying at the end :_;

DO NOT be put off by the pixely graphics - you will probably get used to it after an hour or so and even appreciate it as it fits the atmosphere perfectly.

Charlie, Charlie, Charlie...
